  "texts": [
    "We conjecture that this stems from a mismatch between the tasks, rubrics, and evaluation setups of the external benchmarks vs. what we used for training.",
    "For instance, RL training uses a judge that differs from the judges used in downstream evaluations, which can lead to reward hacking toward preferences specific to the training-time judge.",
    "Moreover, external benchmarks often use expert-crafted or generated rubrics that may emphasize aspects not captured in our training rubrics.",
    "Some rubrics may not be clear from the question alone, making it challenging for models not trained on specific benchmarks.",
    "This underscores the value of fully open DR models like DR Tulu, which can be easily customized for downstream tasks."
  ],
